    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-21T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-21T03:00:00-05:00" n="548"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d548">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/483: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-21T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >December 21, 1930—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 21—7:02 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1065. Legation’s 1064, December 20, 3 p.m. Following from the Minister at
                    Nanking.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“December 20, 11 a.m. Copy of document identical with one in English handed
                        to Wilden<note n="86" xml:id="d548fn86">Henri A. Wilden, French Minister in
                            China.</note> was given to me on the 18th and is going to you by hand of
                            Ingram<note n="87" xml:id="d548fn87">Edward M. B. Ingram, Counselor of
                            British Legation in China.</note> leaving here on Sunday.<note n="88"
                            xml:id="d548fn88">December 21.</note> I have informed French Consul. I
                        understand that similar documents were given to other interested countries
                        but not to the Japanese.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
